A great spot to grab a coffee at the International Airport. It is located in The Quad area as soon as you exit the airport. There is good amount of seating. 

The food is alright, but I prefer the coffees here. They are made quickly and the staff are very kind if you want it heated more or you want some change in it. The place is also reasonably priced for an airport cafe. 

Overall a good experience here.

Café Coffee Day (CCD) is an Indian café chain. It is a subsidiary of Coffee Day Enterprises Limited. Coffee Day serves 1.8 billion cups of coffee annually in six countries
Café Coffee Day Global Limited Company is a Chikkamagaluru-based business which grows coffee in its own estates of 20,000 acres. It is the largest producer of arabica beans in Asia, exporting to various countries including the U.S., Europe, and Japan.

V. G. Siddhartha started the café chain in 1996 when he incorporated Coffee Day Global, which is the parent of the Coffee Day chain. The first CCD outlet was set up on July 11, 1996, at Brigade Road, Bangalore, Karnataka. It rapidly expanded to other cities in India, with more than 1000 cafés open across the nation by 2011.

In 2010, it was announced that a consortium led by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts would invest ₹10 billion (US$140 million) in Coffee Day Resorts, owned by the company.The same year, the logo was changed to the current logo, which the company stated was to showcase the chain as a place to talk.This was done with major changes in the layout of the stores, including the addition of lounges and a total revamp of the interiors.

Café Coffee Day is my daily driver at work. As it is located in an airport, expect it to be overpriced. They offer standard set of items across their outlets. Their Cappuccino and Mocha are top class. They have a good collection of sandwiches - both veg and non veg. I personally love their Smoked Chicken Sandwich. They resemble your regular Subway Sandwiches in terms of form factor. 

They do offer burgers too. Their chicken burger is good. They are juicy and tasty too. 

Chilly cheese toast is best accompanied with a good cappuccino coffee.

They have a good collection of cakes as well. chocolate fantasy is my personal favourite. They are hot favourites as birthday cakes too. 

They have their trademark sizzling brownie too. 

The staffs are courteous and are helpful too. Their setting is good. They offer spacious seating. The overall ambience is good and colourful. 

The Cafe Coffee Day outlets maintain their standard and are consistent with their offerings across the outlets. Quality and hygiene are top priority. You can order a Cappuccino and sit back on their couch with a book, relax and enjoy the time there. It is a good place for hangouts with friends and colleagues too. You can have your own personal space, sit back and relax here.
Café Coffee Day is located inside KIAL (Kempegowda International Airport Limited), Bangalore. They offer sandwiches, coffee and other beverages. Their Cappuccino and Latte are pretty standard and tasty. Items are overpriced, due to the fact that it is inside an international airport terminal.
The BIAL (Bangalore International Airport Limited) is renamed to Kempegowda International Airport Limited (KIAL). It is well maintained and we'll serviced. 
 The Kempegowda International Terminal or the Bangalore international Airport is very plush and majestic. It is one of the best airports in India. They look posh and are well maintained. There are designated spots for passenger pickup and  drop. This is frequented by taxi's, private cars etc to drop off and pick up passengers.  There is a special zone for the Vayu Vajra Airport Volvo buses that ply to and from the airport to every part of the city. The Kempegowda International Airport Bus Station is the designated spot for the Vayu Vajra Airport Volvo buses that ply to and from the airport to every part of the city. There is transit 24x7 from here to the city. There are designated taxi zones for the Online Taxi's like Uber, Ola etc and for the traditional ones too. The passengers can avail the cab service from here. It is right next to the Vayu Vajra bus station.
 This is one of the best airports in India. It maintains the international standards and is beautifully constructed.
